Results_Guess: I think certain movements are expected to follow other movements like we would expect certain beats in a song to follow other meoldies

Exp_Guess: How experience and practice in physical activity, especially sequence/order based physical activity affects someone’s ability to remember or better remember the order of movements
Results_Guess: I think that the more training/practice should have in a sequence based physical activity (like dance or figure skating, where there is an order, not volleyball or something like that) would improve your ability to remember the order of movements.
Strategies: I tried to imitate the movements in the sequence to try to remember what came after (although it didn’t work for me)

Exp_Guess: To test whether receiving formal training in physical activities (both in duration and how recent it was) has an effect on how well you can memorize and duplicate sequences of movements.
Results_Guess: Longer duration and more recent formal training --> better memorization and duplication of movements
